      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A loaf (kikkar).—A round cake (1Samuel 2:36). The parallel in Samuel has a less common word (hallath), meaning a sacrificial cake punctured all over. (Comp. Exodus 29:23.)",
