      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A good piece of flesh.—A single Hebrew term, found only here and in Samuel (’eshpār). It seems to mean “a portion,” i.e., of the victims slain for the “peace offerings.” (The “burnt offerings” were wholly consumed on the altar.) Syriac, “a portion.” Arabic, “a slice of flesh.” Others interpret, “a measure of wine.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "A good piece of flesh.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—A single Hebrew term, found only here and in Samuel (’",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "eshpār",
            "children": []
