  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 3.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - Each little clause of this verse is replete with interest. The royal giver, who now ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "dealt to every one of Israel",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", was, after all, but a channel; yes, and only one channel, through which the fulness and the bounty of the royal Giver of every good and perfect gift, of all good whatsoever, of all things necessary to life and godliness, are supplied to every one of his creature-subjects. But it is highest honour, as servant and instrument alone, to figure forth him in any way. The second little clause tells us either that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "women",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " took a recognized place on occasion of this joyous festival, or that the hospitality of such an occasion did not forget them and their homes. And the following three little clauses require closer examination. The word here translated \"loaf\" in the expression ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "loaf of bread",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "כִּכַּר",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for which in this sense we may turn to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 8:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 2:36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 10:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 6:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 37:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The corresponding word, however, in the parallel place is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "חַלַח",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (for which see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:2, 23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 2:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 7:12, 13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
